data.text:
Fresno State and Air Force meet for a spot in the Mountain West college baseball championship game.

Fresno State and Air Force meet on Saturday afternoon in the Mountain West college baseball tournament, with the winner set to play San Jose State for the overall title. Fresno State lost 3-2 to Air Force on Thursday but bounced back with a 6-1 over New Mexico on Friday. As for Air Force, the team is coming off a 16-9 loss to San Jose State on Friday, sending the team to this game to determine which gets eliminated and which moves on to the final.

In the first meeting of these teams, Air Force got off to a hot start with a three-run first inning. The Falcons wouldn’t score again, but it was enough to propel them to the victory. Jay Thomason hit his 20th home run of the season to drive in two of those three runs, with Chase Spencer homering earlier in the inning for the other. Air Force’s first three batters scored, but Fresno State pitcher Jake Dixon allowed just one more hit after that, going 6.1 innings.
